  "prompt": "How do you pre-select a seat when booking a flight on Royal Air Maroc?",
  "response": "To pre-select a seat when booking a flight on Royal Air Maroc, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. During Booking:\n- When booking your flight on the Royal Air Maroc website, there is typically an option to select your seat during the booking process\n- You can choose your preferred seat from the available seat map\n\n2. After Booking:\n- Log into your booking on the Royal Air Maroc website using your booking reference and last name\n- Navigate to the \"Manage Booking\" or \"Seat Selection\" section\n- Choose your desired seat from the available options\n\n3. Additional Methods:\n- Contact Royal Air Maroc customer service directly\n- Visit their ticket counter at the airport\n- Use their mobile app to select seats\n\nNote: Some seat selections may incur an additional fee, depending on the seat location and your ticket type. Premium seats or seats with extra legroom typically cost more.\n\nIt's recommended to check the specific details and current process on the Royal Air Maroc website or by contacting their customer service for the most up-to-date information.",
